,286,619),(2057,'2017-05-16 16:49:16','2017-05-16 16:49:16','<p>Q.2</p>','/uploads/images/comment-akG5hLYR.JPG',274,619),(2058,'2017-05-17 02:29:14','2017-05-17 02:29:14','<p>Q.7</p>','/uploads/images/comment-2fgVqHK0.JPG',274,619),(2059,'2017-05-17 02:50:52','2017-05-17 02:50:52','<p>Q.8</p>','/uploads/images/comment-yx5cMi95.JPG',274,619),(2060,'2017-05-17 03:01:52','2017-05-17 03:01:52','<p>Q.9</p>','/uploads/images/comment-6RWlwm0T.JPG',274,619),(2061,'2017-05-17 03:15:27','2017-05-17 03:15:27','<p>Q.10</p>','/uploads/images/comment-Tjz15Zv5.JPG',274,619),(2062,'2017-05-17 05:27:33','2017-05-17 05:27:33','<p>Sol2) A piston-cylinder device contains air at a specified state. The air undergoes three processes and we have to determine the boundary work for each of the processes and the network of the cycle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For air take R = 0.287 kJ/kgK and&nbsp;&gamma; = 1.4</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=V_%7B1%7D%3D%5Cfrac%7BmRT%7D%7BP_%7B1%7D%7D\" alt=\"\" /><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=%3D%5Cfrac%7B(0.15)(0.287)(350%2B273)%7D%7B2000kPa%7D\" alt=\"\" /><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=%3D0.01341m%5E%7B3%7D\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Similarly find&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=V_%7B2%7D\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;at&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=P_%7B2%7D\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;to be&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=0.05364m%5E%7B3%7D\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Isothermal work, W<sub>isothermal</sub>=P<sub>1</sub>V<sub>1</sub> ln(V<sub>2</sub>/V<sub>1</sub>) = (2000 kPa)(0.01341 m<sup>3</sup>) ln(0.05364/0.01341) = 37.18 kJ</p>\r\n<p>Find V<sub>3</sub> at the end of polytropic process by using&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=P_%7B2%7DV_%7B2%7D%5E%7Bn%7D%3DP_%7B3%7DV_%7B3%7D%5E%7Bn%7D\" alt=\"\" />, V<sub>3</sub> = 0.016390 m<sup>3</sup>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Polytropic work, W<sub>polytropic</sub> = (P<sub>3</sub>V<sub>3</sub> - P<sub>2</sub>V<sub>2</sub>)/(1-n) = - 34.86kJ</p>\r\n<p>Find the isobaric process, W<sub>isobaric&nbsp;</sub>= P<sub>3</sub>(V<sub>1</sub>-V<sub>3</sub>) = (2000 kPa)(0.01341-0.01690) = -6.97 kJ</p>\r\n<p>Net work for the cycle = 37.18 - 34.86 - 6.97 = -4.65 kJ</p>','',2,619),(2063,'2017-05-17 05:35:44','2017-05-17 05:35:44','<p>Data for sol 3 is as follows:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=P_%7B1%7D%3D160%20kPa\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=x_%7B1%7D%3D0.4\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;from tables it is given</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=v_%7Bf%7D%3D0.0007437\" alt=\"\" />,&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7Bf%7D%3D31.09\" alt=\"\" />,&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=v_%7Bg%7D%3D0.12348\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7Bfg%7D%3D190.27\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Then find&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=v_%7B1%7D%3Dv_%7Bf%7D%3Dx_%7B1%7Dv_%7Bfg%7D\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7B1%7D%3Du_%7Bf%7D%2Bx_%7B1%7Du_%7Bfg%7D\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Now&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=P_%7B2%7D%3D700kPa\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;is in superheated region and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7B2%7D%3D376.99\" alt=\"\" /></p>','',2,619),(2064,'2017-05-17 05:49:18','2017-05-17 05:49:18','<p>Data for sol 4.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Take the entire content of the tank as the system. This will be a closed system. W=Q=KE=PE=0.</p>\r\n<p>For&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=P_%7B1%7D%3D600kPa%20\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=T_%7B1%7D%3D60%5E%7Bo%7DC\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;from tables we have,</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=v_%7B1%7D%3Dv_%7Bfg%4060%5E%7Bo%7DC%7D%3D0.001017\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7B1%7D%3Du_%7Bfg%4060%5E%7Bo%7DC%7D%3D251.16\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Assume that the final state in the tank is a saturated L-V mixture. Now this assumption will be verified if we get the quality between 0 and 1.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=P_%7B2%7D%3D10%20kPa\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7B2%7D%3Du_%7B1%7D\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;from tables we have</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=v_%7Bf%7D%3D0.001010\" alt=\"\" />,&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=u_%7Bf%7D%3D191.79\" alt=\"\" />,&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx&amp;chf=a,s,000000|bg,s,FFFFFF00&amp;chl=v_%7Bg%7D%3D14.670%20m%5E%7B3%7D%2Fkg\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img src=\"https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?cht=tx