INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (29,'2016-06-28 07:09:48','2017-07-05 12:09:57','','article','29','','<h4>Tips to crack GATE - It\'s all about balance</h4>\n<div class=\"all-content\">Yes, <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;preparation requires a lot of hard work and dedication, but one has to be smart about how to approach it. You only have 24 hours in a day and you have to use them efficiently. One of the most common mistakes <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;aspirants make is to indiscriminately&nbsp;solve as many problems as they can. We have often seen students prepare a topic from ten different books. They pick up every book available and just keep solving problems. Practising is great, but <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;is not about merely solving problems. It is a test of your concepts and there is no direct correlation between the number of questions you solve and how conceptually strong you are on a topic. So, don\'t panic if you friends are solving problems from every possible book out there for <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;preparation.&nbsp;</div>\n<div class=\"all-content\">\n<div class=\"art-content\">\n<div class=\"all-content\">\n<p>Don\'t bother picking up substandard books (they will often have wrong solutions).&nbsp;<em>Just focus on understanding the basics and stick to a few recommended books from the best authors there are.</em>&nbsp;Give time to each and every question, especially those which you could not solve in a couple of tries. When you attempt a problem during your <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;preparation, don\'t start solving it right away; build an approach in your head, figure out the underlying principles involved and think how you can apply the concepts and tools that you have learnt so far, to that particular problem. Don\'t just apply the formulae. It will make your thinking shallow and will deprive you of real learning.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Another issue with <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;aspirants is that they keep making the same mistakes over and over again. If we focus on merely doing as many problems as possible, we do not give ourselves time to reflect on our mistakes and revisit the concepts. We just think that the next time we won\'t make the same mistake, but are bound to fail again becuase the underlying concept is flawed, and there are only so many mistakes that one can remember. So, focus on the concepts. If you make a mistake, take some time and reflect on the concept and figure out where you went wrong. Don\'t focus on the number of problems; instead, focus on the problem in problems.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>How many problems are enough while preparing for<a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>?&nbsp;</em>Now you must be wondering how many problems you should solve for a particular concept - 5, 10, 30 or 100? Our answer is that it\'s not really about the number of problems but the type of problems you solve. There has to be a gradual increase in the difficulty level of <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>GATE</strong> </a>problems as you move ahead with a concept. The problems have to involve multiple concepts. You can solve a 1000 problems of the same type and yet be stumped when the <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>&nbsp;exam asks you a slightly twisted problem from the same concept.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Therefore, place a greater focus on solving different types of problems. Ask your friends about the interesting or difficult problems they have encountered in a topic. Bounce problems off them and see their approach, understand their thought process and compare them with yours. Find out a way to learn from your peers and a way to contribute.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In the next article, we keep the tradition alive of motivating you with interesting articles on <a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>GATE</strong></a>preparation and tips to crack<a href=\"https://mindvis.in/courses/gate-2017-mechanical-engineering\" target=\"_blank\">GATE</a>.&nbsp;<em>Cheerio!!!</em></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>',0,'',147,5,2,2,'','',1),(46,'2016-07-06 07:57:32','2017-07-07 19:29:36','Tips and Suggestions to score a 2-Digit Rank (AIR) in GATE 2017 Mechanical Engineering stream','article','46','/static/uploads/images/swmrfmirsgdabapf.jpg','<p>By now you should\'ve set a target for yourself to achieve in GATE 2017. It is good that you have a defined target in terms of 2-digit GATE AIR (All India Rank). Defining a target will always keep you on toes and if you are really dedicated then you will take small steps everyday towards achieving your target.&nbsp; Now what should be those small steps or we can say small tasks. It is a scheduled planning of making and revising notes and practicing the previous year questions.&nbsp;<br /><br />Now the key difference between an average achiever and a top achiever is repetitiveness. The top achievers don\'t stop or get disheartened if they are not able to solve questions. A balance should be maintained in terms of concepts to be understood and concepts to simply <strong>C</strong>ommit <strong>T</strong>o <strong>M</strong>emory. So these two tools of understanding and <strong>CTM</strong> should be used as per the type of topic and questions. Always remember the term <strong>exhaustive practice</strong>.<br /><br />Sitting for hours and staring at the notebook won\'t help you or give you any results. So be&nbsp;<strong>task</strong>&nbsp;<strong>oriented and don\'t call it a day until you complete your day\'s tasks (topics and questions). Completion of task may take 10 min or 10 hours just don\'t procrastinate for the next day.&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />Below given is the list of the key pointers that you should follow aggressively while preparing:<br /><br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Curriculum (Write down syllabus or make excel sheet of topics and sub topics)</li>\n<li>Schedule the task (Make a proper study plan and follow it dedicatedly)</li>\n<li>Segregated lecture notes (After listening to online lectures, make your own hand-written notes)</li>\n<li>Short notes (Create short notes out of your detailed hand-written notes)</li>\n<li>Previous year Question Bank (Solve previous years IES objective and GATE questions)</li>\n<li>Practicing online tests (Give online Mock Tests)</li>\n<li>Introspect on careless mistakes, mark them and revise them.</li>\n<li>Revise short notes and questions bank notebook regularly.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Remember knowledge is essential but it doesn\'t mean to dive deep into the books. Work with some strategy, as GATE is an Engineering aptitude testing exam. So focus on lecture notes only instead of Books to save time and understand the significance of every topic in terms of marks in GATE by practicing tests again and again.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Follow the above said points aggressively. They are definitely going to help you in getting a 2-digit rank in GATE exam!</p>\n<p>All the Best!</p>',0,'',203,5,2,2,'','',1),(47,'2016-07-06 08:03:23','2017-07-10 03:36:37','Solve the question below.','question','47','','<p>A cylindrical resistor element on a circuit board dissipates 0.6 W of power. The resistor is 1.5 cm long, and has a&nbsp;diameter of 0.4 cm. Assuming heat to be transferred uniformly&nbsp;from all surfaces, determine (<em>a</em>) the amount of heat this resistor<br />dissipates during a 24-hour period, (<em>b</em>) the heat flux, and (<em>c</em>) the&nbsp;fraction of heat dissipated from the top and bottom surfaces.</p>',0,'',290,5,2,4,'','',1),(48,'2016-07-06 08:06:27','2017-07-05 11:43:22','Solve the question given below.','question','48','','<p>Infiltration of cold air into a warm house during winter&nbsp;through the cracks around doors, windows, and other openings&nbsp;is a major source of energy loss since the cold air that enters&nbsp;needs to be heated to the room temperature. The infiltration is&nbsp;often expressed in terms of ACH (air changes per hour).</p>\n<p>An ACH of 2 indicates that the entire air in the house is replaced&nbsp;twice every hour by the cold air outside.&nbsp;Consider an electrically heated house that has a floor space&nbsp;of 200 <img title=\"m^{2}\" src=\"https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?m^{2}\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;and an average height of 3 m at 1000 m elevation,&nbsp;where the standard atmospheric pressure is 89.6 kPa. The&nbsp;house is maintained at a temperature of 22&deg;C, and the infiltration losses are estimated to amount to 0.7 ACH. Assuming the&nbsp;pressure and the temperature in the house remain constant, determine the amount of energy loss from the house due to infiltration for a day during which the average outdoor temperature&nbsp;is 5&deg;C. Also, determine the cost of this energy loss for that day&nbsp;if the unit cost of electricity in that area is $0.082/kWh.<br /> </p>',0,'',165,5,2,4,'','',1),(49,'2016-07-06 14:12:57','2017-07-07 01:32:44','Answer the question below on Joule Thomson Coefficient.','question','49','','<p>Why is Joule Thomson coefficient zero for an Ideal gas?</p>',0,'',189,5,2,3,'','',1),(50,'2016-07-07 10:29:21','2017-07-10 00:17:17','Official ISRO Scientist/Engineer Exam ME 2016- Answer Keys released!','article','50','/static/uploads/images/jpipzroudyleajft.png','<p>To check the detailed answer key, click<strong><a href=\"https://www.isro.gov.in/sites/default/files/anskeyweb-mechanical.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"> HERE&nbsp;</a>.&nbsp;</strong></p>',0,'',154,5,2,2,'','',1),(52,'2016-07-08 05:35:38','2017-07-05 12:09:52','UPSC ESE Mechanical Engineering 2017 Syllabus','article','52','/static/uploads/images/cagkdrzixoaprdlb.jpg','<p>Based on the recommendations of Expert Committees formed by the Union Public Service Commission , the Government ( Ministry of Railways) has conveyed its approval to the following Structural changes in the scheme and syllabi of the Engineering Services Examination to be implemented from the year 2017 onwards.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Check out the detailed syllabus<strong><a href=\"https://mindvis.in/articles/upsc-ese-mechanical-engineering-2017-syllabus\" target=\"_blank\"> here.</a></strong></p>',0,'',144,5,2,2,'','',1),(53,'2016-07-11 08:42:44','2017-07-05 11:52:17','Answer the question given below on deflection of beams.','question','53','','<p>When we fix a rope at two points loosely why does it happens that it has a maximum deflexion at centre.and not anywhere else?</p>',0,'',162,5,2,7,'','',1),(54,'2016-07-12 04:41:37','2017-07-07 01:16:04','Answer this question on Heat transfer.','question','54','','<p>The cause of hydrodynamic boundary layer is viscosity. What is the cause of thermal boundary layer?</p>',0,'',152,5,2,4,'','',1),(55,'2016-07-12 05:30:21','2017-07-08 04:12:10','Answer this on Thermal Boundary Layer','question','55','','<p>Air at&nbsp;<img title=\"27^{0}C\" src=\"https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?27^{0}C\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;blows over a flat surface with a sharp edge at 1.5 m/s. Find the B.L thinckness 0.5 m from the leading edge. Check the B.L assumption that u&gt;&gt;v at the trailing edge.</p>',0,'',137,5,2,4,'','',1),(56,'2016-07-12 05:45:43','2017-07-05 11:43:03','Answer this question on BL theory','question','56','','<p>Calculate the average shear stress and the overall friction coefficient for the surface in the question,&nbsp;<a href=\"post/55\">https://geekvis.in/post/55</a>&nbsp;if its total length is L = 0.5 m. Compare&nbsp;<img title=\"\